<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1582]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shape of the proximal mesosome and mesosomal lobes suggest a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microgenitalis" status="new species" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[1351,1382,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1397,1427,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,312,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">microgenitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[319,456,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[319,456,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[471,571,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[212,1362,197,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[206,1382,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) microgenitalis new species ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 3, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 4, male genitalia, dorsal view. 5, male mesosome, ventral view. 6, male paramere, dorsal view. 7, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view.Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; ames = anterior mesosomal seta; as2 = anterior seta 2; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; mts3 = marginal temporal seta 3; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; vms = vulval marginal seta; vos = vulval oblique seta; vss = vulval submarginal seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825551/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 4–6</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[634,837,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saburrata" status="new species" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[634,664,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[681,711,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[727,837,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">saburrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[845,982,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[845,982,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[997,1126,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 11–13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1582]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
These two species can be separated by the following characters: proximal mesosome with slight lateral bulges in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[181,436,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microgenitalis" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[181,211,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[228,258,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[275,436,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">microgenitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[452,520,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[212,1362,197,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[206,1382,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) microgenitalis new species ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 3, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 4, male genitalia, dorsal view. 5, male mesosome, ventral view. 6, male paramere, dorsal view. 7, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view.Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; ames = anterior mesosomal seta; as2 = anterior seta 2; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; mts3 = marginal temporal seta 3; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; vms = vulval marginal seta; vos = vulval oblique seta; vss = vulval submarginal seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825551/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), but without such bulges in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[849,1053,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saburrata" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[849,879,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[896,926,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[943,1053,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">saburrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1070,1154,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); female subgenital plate gently rounded distally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[447,703,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microgenitalis" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[447,478,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[494,525,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[542,703,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">microgenitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[718,787,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[212,1362,197,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[206,1382,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) microgenitalis new species ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 3, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 4, male genitalia, dorsal view. 5, male mesosome, ventral view. 6, male paramere, dorsal view. 7, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view.Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; ames = anterior mesosomal seta; as2 = anterior seta 2; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; mts3 = marginal temporal seta 3; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; vms = vulval marginal seta; vos = vulval oblique seta; vss = vulval submarginal seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825551/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), but broadly flattened distally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1170,1375,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saburrata" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[1170,1201,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1217,1248,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1265,1375,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">saburrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); shape of dorsal fringe and distal margin of mesosome differ between species (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1199,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[212,1362,197,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[206,1382,181,1812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) microgenitalis new species ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 3, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 4, male genitalia, dorsal view. 5, male mesosome, ventral view. 6, male paramere, dorsal view. 7, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view.Abbreviations: ads = anterior dorsal seta; ames = anterior mesosomal seta; as2 = anterior seta 2; dsms = dorsal submarginal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; mts3 = marginal temporal seta 3; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2; vms = vulval marginal seta; vos = vulval oblique seta; vss = vulval submarginal seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825551/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1212,1285,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">11–12</figureCitation>
); male tergopleurite V with 2 
<emphasis box="[350,372,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ss</emphasis>
and male tergopleurites VI–VII with&gt;2 
<emphasis box="[834,856,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ss</emphasis>
on each side in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1039,1294,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microgenitalis" subGenus="Indoceoplanetes">
<emphasis box="[1039,1070,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1086,1117,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1133,1294,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">microgenitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1310,1376,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[238,1341,203,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[220,1367,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) microgenitalis new species ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 1, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 2, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views. Abbreviations: mms = marginal mesometathoracic seta; ps = paratergal seta; psps = principal postspiracular seta; ss = sutural seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825549" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825549/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), but tergopleurite V with 1 
<emphasis box="[404,426,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ss</emphasis>
and tergopleurites VI–VII with 2 
